## Integration Test: CLI flags

We have unit tests but no test that runs the full CLI and checks output.

## What to test

Create `tests/cli.test.js`:

```js
const { execSync } = require('child_process');
const assert = require('assert');

const out = execSync('node index.js --list', { encoding: 'utf8' });
assert.ok(out.includes('Prettier'));
assert.ok(out.includes('Total:'));

const json = JSON.parse(execSync('node index.js --list --json', { encoding: 'utf8' }));
assert.ok(Array.isArray(json) && json.length > 0);

const help = execSync('node index.js --help', { encoding: 'utf8' });
assert.ok(help.includes('Usage'));
```

## Difficulty

Easy-medium.

## Performance: In-memory cache for loadCategories()

`loadCategories()` reads all JSON files from disk every time it is called. Add a simple in-memory cache.

## Proposed change in src/loader.js

```js
let _cache = null;

function loadCategories() {
  if (_cache) return _cache;
  // existing logic
  _cache = result;
  return _cache;
}

function clearCache() { _cache = null; }
module.exports = { ..., clearCache };
```

## Tests to add

- Second call to `loadCategories()` returns the same object reference (`===`)
- `clearCache()` causes the next call to reload from disk
